Package: cohort
Title: Build Analytic Cohorts with Full Provenance
Version: 2026.6.23
Authors@R: c(
  person(c("Richard","Aubrey"), "White", email = "hello@rwhite.no", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6747-1726"))
  )
Description: A framework for building analytic cohorts with full provenance.
    Supports branched cohort trees, per-step exclusion logging with
    human-readable reasons, schema validation at branch boundaries, cached
    derived artifacts on each cohort, and CONSORT diagram generation. The
    framework cleanly separates cohort definition from analysis: it produces
    analytic data tables that downstream packages can consume. A shared-base
    storage strategy keeps memory flat as the cohort tree grows.
